Attribution Notice
==================

This project draws inspiration from, but does not contain code from, the
following projects. If you contribute code derived from any of them, ensure
license compatibility and update this notice.

- OpenClaw (Steinberger) — MIT-licensed.
  Inspired: `workspace/skills/<name>/SKILL.md` pattern; the
  CLAUDE.md / AGENTS.md / SOUL.md / TOOLS.md document separation;
  Local-First-Gateway / Companion-App pattern.

- Hermes Agent (NousResearch) — Apache-2.0.
  Inspired: FTS5-based session search with LLM summarization (see ADR-0025);
  ThreadPoolExecutor parallel tool-call pattern (adapted to Promise.all in TS).
  Note: the ProviderTransport-ABC pattern from Hermes was explicitly NOT
  adopted here — see ADR-0003 for the claude.exe-delegation decision.

- Claude Code / Anthropic SDK — Anthropic-licensed.
  The bundled `bin/claude.exe` binary is included as a runtime dependency.
  See ADR-0003 (Hybrid-CLI Delegation) and ADR-0011 (Anthropic-CLI Auth
  Integration) for the delegation contract.

- Tauri 2.x — MIT / Apache-2.0 dual-licensed.
  Used as the GUI framework (ADR-0001) and Sidecar IPC layer (ADR-0006).

- `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk` — MIT.
  Used for MCP-Server and Tool-Registry (ADR-0007 / ADR-0016).

- `@napi-rs/keyring` — MIT.
  Used for OS-Keychain integration (ADR-0004).

- `@sinclair/typebox` — MIT.
  Used for schema validation (ADR-0012).

For private repos derived from or depending on this codebase
(`claude-os-msp`, `house-watch` — see ADR-0030), the MIT license of this
codebase applies to the consumed portions. The private repos themselves
remain proprietary ("All rights reserved" by default) per ADR-0029.
